          "type": "text",
          "text": "1. Overview"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The stored procedure "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "usp_Information_BeforeDataTransformationAndProcess",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " is designed to perform a validation check on account data before it undergoes further data transformation and processing. It identifies accounts with invalid billing periods by comparing the billing period revision of each account against the current processing period. The procedure retrieves and returns a list of accounts that have either a null billing period revision, a billing period revision greater than the current processing period, or a null value for the first period canceled."
        }
      ]
    },
